      <description>&lt;h3 id=&#34;extension-of-the-tfimageresize_bilinear-to-the-n-dimensional-case&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Extension of the tf.image.resize_bilinear to the N dimensional case&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#extension-of-the-tfimageresize_bilinear-to-the-n-dimensional-case&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Visit the github repository for the full code. &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/viclule/image_resize_n_linear&#34;&gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The function extends the functionality of tf.image.resize_bilinear for N dimensional Tensors.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;strategy&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Strategy&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#strategy&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The strategy is fairly simple, tensors are interpolated two dimensions at a time using the already existant tf.image.resize_bilinear function.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;../../images/posts/multilinear_interpolation_tensorflow_2.png&#34; alt=&#34;Strategy&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;test&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Test&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#test&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Building a 3D volume using a black image, an android image and a white image. [1, 245, 206, 3, 4] [1 batch, height, width, depth, 4 channels]&lt;/p&gt;</description>
